{"lemma":"نَزٌّ","slug":"نَزٌّ","root":"ن.ز.ز","root_slug":"ن-ز-ز","root_link":"/words/roots/ن-ز-ز","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n39645"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%86%D9%8E%D8%B2%D9%8C%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n39645","headword_ar":"نَزٌّ","root":"nz","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niz~N","text_ar":"نِزٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Water that exudes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"oozes, from the ground:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flowing moisture:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) the latter is the better word; and is [said to be] Persian, arabicized: (TA:) the former is an inf. n. used as a subst. (Msb.) ―         -b2-  [The pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuzuwzN","text_ar":"نُزُوزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", occurring in the TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"E*w","text_ar":"عذو"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b3-  [The former is also used as an epithet: fem. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":". You say,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroDN naz~apN","text_ar":"اَرْضٌ نَزَّةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Ground,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"land, having water exuding,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"oozing, from it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aAtu naz~K","text_ar":"ذَاتُ نَزٍّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAz~apN","text_ar":"نَازَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Lh, TA.)       -A2-  [Hence, perhaps,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naz~N","text_ar":"نَزٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"liberal, bountiful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"munificent."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sgh, K.)       -A3-  Also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naz~N","text_ar":"نَزٌّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Much,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"many."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)       -A4-  A man (A'Obeyd, S)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"light,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"active,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A'Obeyd, S, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"light in spirit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sharp in mind,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A'Obeyd, S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clever,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ingenious,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A'Obeyd, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and intel-ligent."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A'Obeyd, TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Light, inconstant, fickle,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unsteady:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) an epithet of dispraise. (TA.) ―         -b3-  A man (TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"much,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"often, in motion;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"minaz~N","text_ar":"مِنَزٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) a man, (A,) and an ostrich, (S, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that does not remain still in one place:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is quick,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"swift, and does not remain still in one place:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or an ostrich, and an antelope,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that leaps, jumps, springs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bounds:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) and a"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"light,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or an"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"active,"},{"kind":"text","text":"camel; (TA;) and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naz~apN","text_ar":"نَزَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", applied to a she-camel. (S, TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Light"},{"kind":"text","text":"dust. (TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ar~K","text_ar":"شَرٍّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niz~u","text_ar":"نِزُّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naziyzuhu","text_ar":"نَزِيزُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liz~uhu","text_ar":"لِزُّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laziyzuhu","text_ar":"لَزِيزُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lz","text_ar":"لز"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","Msb","TA","A"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D9%86%D8%B2/","headword_ar":"نز","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_32","lexicon_en":"Supplément aux dictionnaires arabes by Reinhart Dozy (d. 1883 CE)","lexicon_ar":"تكملة المعاجم العربية لرينهارت دوزي","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=53111#b024cd","body_html":"نز: نز: نعت للأرض التي تنضج ماء (ابن العوام 1: 59).<br>نرز: عامية نز (محيط المحيط)، سيلان، (بوشر).<br>نزارة: ارض التي تنضج ماء (محيط المحيط)."},{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_36","lexicon_en":"Al-Ṣāḥib bin ʿAbbād, Al-Muḥīṭ fī l-Lugha (d. c. 995 CE)","lexicon_ar":"المحيط في اللغة للصاحب بن عباد","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=53111#eed155","body_html":"<span class=\"title1\">نز</span><br><span>النَّز: ما تَحَلبَ من الأرْضِ من الماء. وأنَزتِ الأرْضُ: صارَتْ ذاتَ نَز. وهو النز أيضاً.</span><br><span>وظَلِيْم نَز: لا يَكَادُ يَسْتَقِر في مَكانٍ. والسخِي، والخَفِيْفُ: نَز. والمَنَزُّ: تَمْهِيْدُ الصبِي. وتُرَابٌ نَز: كثير. والنزَانِزُ: القَرِيْعُ من الفُحُوْل. والنًزْنَزَةُ: تَحْرِيْكُ الرأسَ. ونَزِيْزُ الوَتَرِ: اضْطِرَابُه عِنْدَ الرمْيِ. والنَّزِيْزُ: العَدْوُ والقَفْزِ. ونَز الظبْيُ في صَوْتِه نزِيْزاً. ونَزَّ فلانٌ عنّي: انْفَرَدَ جانِباً. والمُنَازةُ: مِثْلُ المُعَازةِ والمُنَافَسَةِ.</span><br><span>والنَزَّةُ: الشَّهْوَةُ. والنَزِيْزُ: الشَّهْوَانُ، وهو الظَّرِيْفُ أيضاً. والظَبْيَةُ تُنَززُ وَلَدَها: أي تَرُبُّه طِفْلاً. ونَززَه عن كذا ونَزَّهَه: بِمَعْنىً. والإنْزَازُ: التَّصَلُّبُ والتَّشَدُّدُ.</span>"},{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_49","lexicon_en":"Arabic-English Lexicon by Edward William Lane (d. 1876)","lexicon_ar":"المعجم العربي الإنجليزي لإدوارد وليام لين","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=53111#1681c6","body_html":"<h3>نز</h3><span class=\"sense\">1</span> نَزَّتِ الأَرْضُ, (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) <abbr title=\"aorist (shows the vowel of the second consonant of the aorist/muḍāriʿ form)\">aor.</abbr> ـِ <abbr title=\"infinitive noun, مَصْدَرٌ\">inf. n.</abbr> نَزٌّ; (<abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>;) and ↓ انزّت, (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>,) The ground, or land, had water exuding, or oozing, from it: (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>:) or had much flowing moisture: (<abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>:) or became [abundant in] مَنَابِع [or places welling forth water], as in the <abbr title=\"The Takmilah fī l-Ṣiḥāḥ of al-Saghānī\">TS</abbr> and the <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>, or مَنَاقِع [or places of stagnant water] by reason of the نَزّ. (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b2:</span> [نَزَّتْ بِهِ البِطْنَةُ: see نِطْنَة.]<br><br><span class=\"sub-sense\">A2:</span> نَزَّ, <abbr title=\"aorist (shows the vowel of the second consonant of the aorist/muḍāriʿ form)\">aor.</abbr> ـِ <abbr title=\"infinitive noun, مَصْدَرٌ\">inf. n.</abbr> نَزِيزٌ, He (an antelope, <abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>,) ran: (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>:) or he (an ostrich, and an antelope,) leaped, jumped, sprang, or bounded. (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b2:</span> He (an antelope, <abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>,) uttered a cry, or cries. (Ibn-El-Jarráh, <abbr title=\"al-Kisāʾī\">Ks</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.) 4 أَنْزَ3َ see 1, first signification.<br><br>نَزٌّ and ↓ نِزٌّ Water that exudes, or oozes, from the ground: (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>:) or flowing moisture: (<abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>:) the latter is the better word; and is [said to be] Persian, arabicized: (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>:) the former is an <abbr title=\"infinitive noun, مَصْدَرٌ\">inf. n.</abbr> used as a <abbr title=\"substantive, إِسْمٌ\">subst.</abbr> (<abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b2:</span> [The <abbr title=\"plural, جَمْعٌ\">pl.</abbr> is نُزُوزٌ, occurring in the <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr> in art. عذو.] <span class=\"sub-sense\">b3:</span> [The former is also used as an <abbr title=\"نَعْتٌ and وَصْفٌ and صِفَةٌ\">epithet</abbr>: <abbr title=\"feminine, مؤَنَّثٌ\">fem.</abbr> with ة. You say,] أَرْضٌ نَزَّةٌ Ground, or land, having water exuding, or oozing, from it; <abbr title=\"synonym and synonymous, مَرَادفٌ and مَتَرَادِفٌ\">syn.</abbr> ذَاتُ نَزٍّ; as also ↓ نَازَّةٌ. (<abbr title=\"El-Lihyanee (Abu al-Ḥasan al-Liḥyānī)\">Lh</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">A2:</span> [Hence, perhaps,] نَزٌّ also signifies (assumed <abbr title=\"مَجَازٌ and مَجَازِيٌّ\">tropical</abbr>:) liberal, bountiful, or munificent. (<abbr title=\"al-Saghānī, author of the ʿUbāb and the Takmilah fī al-Ṣiḥāḥ\">Sgh</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">A3:</span> Also, نَزٌّ Much, or many. (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">A4:</span> A man (<abbr title=\"Abu ʿUbayd (al-Qāsim bin Salām)\">A'Obeyd</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>) light, or active, (<abbr title=\"Abu ʿUbayd (al-Qāsim bin Salām)\">A'Obeyd</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) or light in spirit, (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>,) sharp in mind, (<abbr title=\"Abu ʿUbayd (al-Qāsim bin Salām)\">A'Obeyd</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) clever, or ingenious, (<abbr title=\"Abu ʿUbayd (al-Qāsim bin Salām)\">A'Obeyd</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) and intel-ligent. (<abbr title=\"Abu ʿUbayd (al-Qāsim bin Salām)\">A'Obeyd</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b2:</span> Light, inconstant, fickle, or unsteady: (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>:) an <abbr title=\"نَعْتٌ and وَصْفٌ and صِفَةٌ\">epithet</abbr> of dispraise. (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b3:</span> A man (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>) much, or often, in motion; as also ↓ مِنَزٌّ: (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>:) a man, (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>,) and an ostrich, (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>,) that does not remain still in one place: (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>:) or that is quick, or swift, and does not remain still in one place: (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>:) or an ostrich, and an antelope, that leaps, jumps, springs, or bounds: (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>:) and a light, or an active, camel; (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>;) and so نَزَّةٌ, applied to a she-camel. (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b4:</span> Light dust. (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b5:</span> شَرٍّ ↓ نِزُّ, and ↓ نَزِيزُهُ, <abbr title=\"idem quod (i.e. the same as)\">i. q.</abbr> لِزُّهُ and لَزِيزُهُ. (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>, art. لز.) نِزٌّ: see نَزٌّ.<br><br>نَزِيزٌ: see نَزٌّ, last sentence.<br><br>نَازٌّ: <abbr title=\"feminine, مؤَنَّثٌ\">fem.</abbr> with ة: see نَزٌّ.<br><br>مِنَزٌّ A child's cradle: (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>:) because of its frequent motion. (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b2:</span> See also نَزٌّ."}]}}